1.一种风光储新能源电站黑启动控制方法，其特征在于，包括：1. a black-start control method for wind-solar storage new energy power station, is characterized in that, comprises:


 当电网出现故障且风光储新能源电站具备黑启动条件时，控制储能系统在一定时间内持续设定的电压参考值输出电压，对供电母线电压和频率进行恢复，直到供电母线电压和频率达到额定值；When the power grid fails and the wind-solar-storage new energy power station has the black start condition, the energy storage system is controlled to continuously set the voltage reference value output voltage within a certain period of time, and the power supply bus voltage and frequency are restored until the power supply bus voltage and frequency reach rated value;


 所述供电母线电压和频率达到额定值后，基于风光储的协调控制方法对风电机组、光伏机组和储能电池供电进行控制，实现对负荷的稳定供电。After the voltage and frequency of the power supply bus reach the rated value, the wind turbine, photovoltaic unit and energy storage battery power supply is controlled based on the wind-solar-storage coordinated control method to achieve stable power supply to the load.

2.如权利要求1所述的方法，其特征在于，所述基于风光储的协调控制方法对风电机组、光伏机组和储能电池供电进行控制，实现对负荷的稳定供电，包括：2. The method according to claim 1, wherein the coordinated control method based on wind-solar storage controls the power supply of wind turbines, photovoltaics and energy storage batteries to achieve stable power supply to the load, comprising:


 A1确定光伏机组和风电机组的初始投入数量，按照初始投入数量投入光伏机组和风电机组并接入负荷；A1 Determine the initial input quantity of photovoltaic units and wind turbines, and input photovoltaic units and wind turbines according to the initial input quantity and connect to the load;


 A2采集光伏机组输出功率、风电机组输出功率、负荷用电功率和储能电池的荷电状态；A2 collects the output power of the photovoltaic unit, the output power of the wind turbine, the load power and the state of charge of the energy storage battery;


 A3基于所述光伏机组输出功率、风电机组输出功率、负荷用电功率和储能电池的荷电状态数据，判断系统功率余亏值的绝对值是否大于储能电池出力额定值：A3 is based on the output power of the photovoltaic unit, the output power of the wind turbine, the load power and the state-of-charge data of the energy storage battery, and determines whether the absolute value of the system power residual deficit value is greater than the output rated value of the energy storage battery:


 若大于储能电池出力额定值调整光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量，返回步骤A2；If it is greater than the output rating of the energy storage battery, adjust the input quantity of the photovoltaic unit and the wind turbine, and return to step A2;


 若小于或等于出储能电池出力额定值，执行步骤A4；If it is less than or equal to the output rated value of the energy storage battery, go to step A4;


 A4基于储能电池的荷电状态约束，调整光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量及调整储能电池的充放电状态；A4 adjusts the input quantity of photovoltaic units and wind turbines and adjusts the state of charge and discharge of the energy storage battery based on the state-of-charge constraints of the energy storage battery;


 A5重复执行步骤A2-A5，直到实现对负荷的稳定供电；A5 repeats steps A2-A5 until stable power supply to the load is achieved;


 所述系统功率余亏值等于光伏机组与风电机组的输出功率之和减去负荷用电功率。The system power surplus and deficit value is equal to the sum of the output power of the photovoltaic unit and the wind turbine unit minus the load electric power.

3.如权利要求2所述的方法，其特征在于，所述基于储能电池的荷电状态约束，调整光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量及调整储能电池的充放电状态，包括：3. The method according to claim 2, wherein, adjusting the input quantity of photovoltaic units and wind turbines and adjusting the charge-discharge state of the energy storage battery based on the state-of-charge constraint of the energy storage battery, comprising:


 B1判断光伏机组和风电机组输出功率之和是否大于等于负荷用电功率：B1 judges whether the sum of the output power of photovoltaic units and wind turbines is greater than or equal to the load power:


 若否大于等于负荷用电功率，执行步骤B2；If it is not greater than or equal to the load electric power, go to step B2;


 若否小于负荷用电功率，执行步骤B3；If it is not less than the load electric power, go to step B3;


 B2判断储能电池的荷电状态是否小于设定的最大阈值：若小于设定的最大阈值，控制储能电池充电，并返回步骤A2；若大于等于设定的最大阈值，减少光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量，并返回步骤A2；B2 judges whether the state of charge of the energy storage battery is less than the set maximum threshold: if it is less than the set maximum threshold, control the charging of the energy storage battery, and return to step A2; if it is greater than or equal to the set maximum threshold, reduce photovoltaic units and wind power The input quantity of the unit, and return to step A2;


 B3判断储能电池的荷电状态是否大于设定的最小阈值：若大于设定的最小阈值，控制储能电池放电，并返回步骤A2；若小于等于设定的最小阈值，增加光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量，并返回步骤A2。B3 determines whether the state of charge of the energy storage battery is greater than the set minimum threshold: if it is greater than the set minimum threshold, control the discharge of the energy storage battery, and return to step A2; if it is less than or equal to the set minimum threshold, increase the photovoltaic units and wind power The input quantity of the unit, and return to step A2.

5.如权利要求2所述的方法，其特征在于，在步骤A1之后且步骤A2之前，还包括：5. The method according to claim 2, characterized in that, after step A1 and before step A2, further comprising:


 对光伏机组输出功率采用恒功率控制；Adopt constant power control for the output power of photovoltaic units;


 对风电机组输出功率采用虚拟惯量控制和桨距角控制；Adopt virtual inertia control and pitch angle control for the output power of wind turbine;


 对储能电池输出功率采用电压/频率控制。The output power of the energy storage battery is controlled by voltage/frequency.

6.如权利要求5所述的方法，其特征在于，所述对风电机组输出功率采用虚拟惯量控制和桨距角控制，包括：6. The method according to claim 5, wherein the virtual inertia control and the pitch angle control are adopted for the output power of the wind turbine, comprising:


 当系统负荷投入频率下降时，采用虚拟惯量控制风电机组的双馈电机释放转子动能，进行系统暂态有功支撑；When the input frequency of the system load decreases, the virtual inertia is used to control the DFIG of the wind turbine to release the kinetic energy of the rotor to carry out the transient active support of the system;


 当所述双馈电机转子转速恢复时，通过桨距角控制风机叶片的桨距角吸收风力，进行系统稳态有功支撑。When the rotor speed of the DFIG is restored, the pitch angle of the fan blades is controlled by the pitch angle to absorb the wind force, and the steady-state active support of the system is performed.

9.一种风光储新能源电站黑启动控制系统，其特征在于，包括：9. A black-start control system for a wind-solar-storage new energy power station, characterized in that it comprises:


 自启动模块，用于当电网出现故障且风光储新能源电站具备黑启动条件时，控制储能系统在一定时间内持续设定的电压参考值输出电压，对供电母线电压和频率进行恢复，直到供电母线电压和频率达到额定值；The self-starting module is used to control the output voltage of the energy storage system to continuously set the voltage reference value within a certain period of time, and restore the voltage and frequency of the power supply bus when the power grid fails and the wind-solar-storage new energy power station has the black start condition. The power supply bus voltage and frequency reach the rated value;


 协调供电模块，用于所述供电母线电压和频率达到额定值后，基于风光储的协调控制方法对风电机组、光伏机组和储能电池供电进行控制，实现对负荷的稳定供电。The coordinated power supply module is used to control the power supply of wind turbines, photovoltaics and energy storage batteries based on the coordinated control method of wind-solar storage after the voltage and frequency of the power supply bus reaches the rated value, so as to realize stable power supply to the load.

10.如权利要求9所述的系统，其特征在于，所述协调供电模块，包括：10. The system of claim 9, wherein the coordinated power supply module comprises:


 初始供电模块，用于确定光伏机组和风电机组的初始投入数量，按照初始投入数量投入光伏机组和风电机组并接入负荷；The initial power supply module is used to determine the initial input quantity of photovoltaic units and wind turbines, and input photovoltaic units and wind turbines according to the initial input quantity and connect to the load;


 检测模块，用于采集光伏机组输出功率、风电机组输出功率、负荷用电功率和储能电池的荷电状态；The detection module is used to collect the output power of the photovoltaic unit, the output power of the wind turbine, the load power and the state of charge of the energy storage battery;


 第一判协调模块，用于基于所述光伏机组输出功率、风电机组输出功率、负荷用电功率和储能电池的荷电状态数据，判断系统功率余亏值的绝对值是否大于储能电池出力额定值：The first judgment and coordination module is used for judging whether the absolute value of the system power surplus deficit value is greater than the output rating of the energy storage battery based on the output power of the photovoltaic unit, the output power of the wind turbine, the load electric power and the state of charge data of the energy storage battery value:


 若大于储能电池出力额定值调整光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量，返回检测模块；If it is greater than the output rating of the energy storage battery, adjust the input quantity of the photovoltaic unit and the wind turbine, and return to the detection module;


 若小于或等于出储能电池出力额定值，执行第二协调模块；If it is less than or equal to the output rated value of the energy storage battery, execute the second coordination module;


 第二协调模块，用于基于储能电池的荷电状态约束，调整光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量及调整储能电池的充放电状态；The second coordination module is used to adjust the input quantity of photovoltaic units and wind turbines and adjust the charge-discharge state of the energy storage battery based on the state-of-charge constraint of the energy storage battery;


 循环模块，用于重复执行检测模块、第一判协调模块、第二协调模块和循环模块步骤，直到实现对负荷的稳定供电；The circulation module is used to repeatedly execute the steps of the detection module, the first judgment coordination module, the second coordination module and the circulation module until the stable power supply to the load is achieved;


 所述系统功率余亏值等于光伏机组与风电机组的输出功率之和减去负荷用电功率。The system power surplus and deficit value is equal to the sum of the output power of the photovoltaic unit and the wind turbine unit minus the load electric power.

11.如权利要求10所述的系统，其特征在于，所述第二协调模块，包括：11. The system of claim 10, wherein the second coordination module comprises:


 第一判断模块，用于判断光伏机组和风电机组输出功率之和是否大于等于负荷用电功率：The first judging module is used to judge whether the sum of the output power of the photovoltaic unit and the wind turbine is greater than or equal to the load electric power:


 若否大于等于负荷用电功率，执行步骤B2；If it is not greater than or equal to the load electric power, go to step B2;


 若否小于负荷用电功率，执行步骤B3；If it is not less than the load electric power, go to step B3;


 第二判断模块，用于判断储能电池的荷电状态是否小于设定的最大阈值：若小于设定的最大阈值，控制储能电池充电，并返回检测模块步骤；若大于等于设定的最大阈值，减少光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量，并返回检测模块步骤；The second judgment module is used to judge whether the state of charge of the energy storage battery is less than the set maximum threshold: if it is less than the set maximum threshold, control the charging of the energy storage battery, and return to the step of the detection module; if it is greater than or equal to the set maximum threshold Threshold, reduce the input quantity of photovoltaic units and wind turbines, and return to the detection module step;


 第三判断模块，用于判断储能电池的荷电状态是否大于设定的最小阈值：若大于设定的最小阈值，控制储能电池放电，并返回检测模块步骤；若小于等于设定的最小阈值，增加光伏机组和风电机组的投入数量，并返回检测模块步骤。The third judgment module is used to judge whether the state of charge of the energy storage battery is greater than the set minimum threshold: if it is greater than the set minimum threshold, control the discharge of the energy storage battery, and return to the step of the detection module; if it is less than or equal to the set minimum threshold Threshold, increase the input quantity of photovoltaic units and wind turbines, and return to the detection module step.

13.如权利要求10所述的系统，其特征在于，所述协调供电模块，还包括：13. The system of claim 10, wherein the coordinated power supply module further comprises:


 光伏输出功率控制模块，用于对光伏机组输出功率采用恒功率控制；The photovoltaic output power control module is used to control the output power of photovoltaic units with constant power;


 风电输出功率控制模块，用于对风电机组输出功率采用虚拟惯量控制和桨距角控制；The wind power output power control module is used for virtual inertia control and pitch angle control for the output power of the wind turbine;


 储能电池输出功率控制模块，用于对储能电池输出功率采用电压/频率控制。The energy storage battery output power control module is used to control the output power of the energy storage battery by voltage/frequency.

14.如权利要求13所述的系统，其特征在于，所述风电输出功率控制模块，包括：14. The system of claim 13, wherein the wind power output power control module comprises:


 虚拟惯量控制模块，用于当系统负荷投入频率下降时，采用虚拟惯量控制风电机组的双馈电机释放转子动能，进行系统暂态有功支撑；The virtual inertia control module is used to use virtual inertia to control the doubly-fed motor of the wind turbine to release the kinetic energy of the rotor when the input frequency of the system load decreases, and perform the transient active support of the system;


 桨距角控制模块，用于当所述双馈电机转子转速恢复时，通过桨距角控制风机叶片的桨距角吸收风力，进行系统稳态有功支撑。The pitch angle control module is used for absorbing wind force by controlling the pitch angle of the fan blade through the pitch angle when the rotational speed of the rotor of the doubly-fed motor recovers, so as to perform steady-state active support of the system.
